ABSTRACT
A method for generating a geographically-bound mobile ad
hoc network identification. The method may include receiv-
ing, by a processor, a mobile ad hoc network request. The
method may also include determining a plurality of geo-
graphic coordinates of a device associated with a current
location of the device. The method may further include
generating a mobile ad hoc network identification based on
the determined plurality of geographic coordinates. The
method may also include processing the received mobile ad
hoc network request using the generated mobile ad hoc
network identification.
